Sentencas: Composites formed by infiltration of 45 wt % La(0.3)Sr(0.7)TiO(3) (LST) into 65% porous yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) were examined for application as solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anodes.
Titulo: SOFC anodes based on infiltration of La0.3Sr0.7TiO3

Sentencas: Although LST does not react with YSZ, the structure of the LST deposits was strongly affected by the calcination temperature.
Titulo: SOFC anodes based on infiltration of La0.3Sr0.7TiO3

Sentencas: At 1373 K, the LST formed loosely packed, 0.1 mu m particles that filled the YSZ pores.
Titulo: SOFC anodes based on infiltration of La0.3Sr0.7TiO3

Sentencas: The conductivity of this composite depended strongly on the pretreatment conditions but was greater than 0.4 S/cm after heating to 1173 K in humidified (3% H(2)O) H(2).
Titulo: SOFC anodes based on infiltration of La0.3Sr0.7TiO3

Sentencas: Following calcination at 1573 K, the LST had sintered significantly, decreasing the conductivity of the composite by a factor of approximately 5.
Titulo: SOFC anodes based on infiltration of La0.3Sr0.7TiO3

Sentencas: The addition of a catalyst was critical for achieving reasonable electrochemical performance, with the addition of 0.5 wt % Pd and 5 wt % ceria increasing the power density of otherwise identical cells from less than 20 to 780 mW/cm(2) for operation in humidified (3% H(2)O) H(2) at 1073 K. Electrodes prepared from LST deposits calcined at 1373 K were found to exhibit a much better performance than those prepared from LST deposits calcined at 1573 K, demonstrating that the structure of the composite is critical for achieving high performance.
Titulo: SOFC anodes based on infiltration of La0.3Sr0.7TiO3
